.\"======================================================================
.Sh SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
This command is intended for local development, but is secured such that it
could be used in production if desired
.Pq "fronted by a proxy which performs HTTPS termination" .
.Pp
Dotfiles and tilde-files are hidden by default
.Po
except
.Qq .well-known
.Pc ,
and the server is protected against directory traversal attacks.
See
.Lk https://github.com/davidje13/web-listener/blob/HEAD/docs/SECURITY.md
for a full analysis of the protections provided by
.Nm .
.Pp
Do not use untrusted input as configuration.
Doing so may result in exposure of sensitive files or arbitrary code execution.
